<p><em>Her Majesty, by and with the advice and consent of the House of Commons of Canada, enacts as follows:</em></p>



<h3 id="part-i-general">Part I: General</h3>

<h4 id="short-title-1">Short Title</h4>

<ol>
<li>This Act may be cited as the <em>Constitution Act</em>.</li>
</ol>



<h4 id="constitution-of-model-canada">Constitution of Model Canada</h4>

<ol>
<li>Model Canada consists of the Head Moderator, the Speaker of the House of Commons, the House of Commons and other institutions established by an Act of Parliament, including this Act, according to the <em>Constitution</em>.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="laws-from-real-life">Laws from Real Life</h4>

<ol>
<li>All Acts of Parliament and the provincial legislatures in real life, all regulations and orders issued by the Government of Canada and the provincial governments in real life, all rulings of the Speaker of the House of Commons in real life, and all judgments of the Supreme Court of Canada in real life before August 2, 2015, and the common law are effective in Model Canada, as applicable to Model Canada and subject to the laws, regulations, orders, rulings and other rules in Model Canada.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="interpretation">Interpretation</h4>

<ol>
<li>In this Constitution: <br>
<ol><li>the House of Commons of Model Canada is referred to as the House of Commons or the House; <br>
the Speaker, unless otherwise specified or required by context, refers to the Speaker of the House;</li>
<li>provisions relying on the creation of the Senate or the Supreme Court are to be interpreted as such that the part of the provisions relying on the creation shall become effective if the House chooses to establish a Senate or Supreme Court, except in cases relating to duties of the Supreme Court as a whole;</li>
<li>unless specified with “in real life” or other words with similar effect, all institutions refer to institutions in Model Canada.</li></ol></li>
</ol></div></body>
